<h2>Status Code Results</h2>

<p>ASP.NET Core can return many common HTTP status codes as dedicated results.  These include:</p>

<ul>
    <li><a asp-action="OkResult">200 OK</a></li>
    <li><a asp-action="CreatedResult">201 Created</a></li>
    <li><a asp-action="NoContentResult">204 No Content</a></li>
    <li><a asp-action="BadRequestResult">400 Bad Request</a></li>
    <li><a asp-action="NotFoundResult">404 Not Found</a></li>
    <li><a asp-action="UnsupportedMediaTypeResult">415 Unsupported Media Type</a></li>
</ul>

<p>ASP.NET Core can also return a generic StatusCodeResult, which can return any of the myriad HTTP status codes, such as:</p>

<ul>
    <li><a asp-action="StatusCodeResult" asp-route-statusCode="410">410 Gone</a></li>
    <li><a asp-action="StatusCodeResult" asp-route-statusCode="451">451 Unavailable For Legal Reasons</a></li>
    <li><a asp-action="StatusCodeResult" asp-route-statusCode="418">418 I'm a Teapot</a></li>
</ul>
